values:
Ginger's funeral was last Saturday.&nbsp; Visitation was from 11-1 and the family had to arrive at 10am.&nbsp; Kaitlin went and looked a Grandma in the casket and then came and whispered to me, "How come they won't let us see&nbsp;Gramma's feet"?&nbsp; I told her I didn't know,&nbsp;but they always keep the bottom half of the casket closed.&nbsp; Apparently that didn't satisfy her, so she approached the&nbsp;funeral director and&nbsp;asked her why she couldn't see her Gramma's face.&nbsp; So, in the middle of the visitation, the funeral director opened the casket up all the way and moved all the satin covering to show Kaitlin Gramma's feet!&nbsp;&nbsp;She then went on to answer every single question Kait had about how the body was treated and how they made Gramma look so good after being so sick.&nbsp; Kaitlin then told me that Gramma died on her side, so they had to mush her face back into shape!&nbsp; OOOOOOOWWWWWWW, more information than I&nbsp;REALLY wanted to know!

During the funeral, northern Illinois was hit with an ice storm so we ended up having to spend another night at Ginger's house.&nbsp; The boys then took the stuff they wanted and we were all off by Sunday morning.&nbsp; We missed the worst of the ice, but because we&nbsp;weren't home to shovel our driveway is a sheet of ice.&nbsp; Winter has definitely arrived in Rockford!&nbsp; Today the wind chill was -14F.&nbsp; For those of you in the warm parts of the world-that is freakin cold!!!!&nbsp; It&nbsp;snowed 6" yesterday and we're supposed to get another 4" tomorrow.&nbsp; I'll never get&nbsp;the driveway cleared at this point.&nbsp; Ordinarily, this wouldn't be a problem, but we're having company over on Saturday and they won't be able to walk up the driveway without sliding back&nbsp;down! LOL.

Tomorrow is Donuts with Dad at Kait's school.&nbsp; They have to be there&nbsp;at 7:15 am.&nbsp; It's good to be the Mom this time.&nbsp; This Sunday we make another trip to Ottawa to help the family empty out the rest of Ginger's house so we can put it on the market.&nbsp; 17 days until I get to hug my grandbabies.&nbsp; I'm so excited if I had a tail it&nbsp;would fall off from wagging!&nbsp;

Well, John got a phone call today telling him he didn't get the&nbsp; job at&nbsp;the Register Star.&nbsp; He is&nbsp;so depressed, he just kept apologizing to me.&nbsp; He feels like he is not a good provider and he is letting us all down.&nbsp; I can't convince him that&nbsp;it's not the case at all.&nbsp;&nbsp;He is here to care for Kaiti when she gets home from school and keep the house up as well as working part time to bring in some income.&nbsp; I feel so bad&nbsp;for him.&nbsp; We are really hurting financially, but no worse than before.&nbsp; We've gotten our bills down to the house payment, utilities, phone, groceries, gasoline, and insurance.&nbsp; I'm not sure where we can cut anymore.&nbsp;&nbsp;

On the work front for me, I had a former client bring in a bunch of winter coats for other families and she was so proud she was showing each one to me.&nbsp; As she did that, a roach came flying out of the box.&nbsp; As soon as she left the custodian came and made the box and&nbsp; coats disappear&nbsp; for me.&nbsp; I haven't been able to find the rogue roach, though.
After that, another woman came in to get clothes for her daughters.&nbsp; She had just come home from the hospital 3 days ago after having her ovaries removed.&nbsp; She has ovarian cancer and they think it's gone into her lymphatic system.&nbsp; Anyway, she did too much and started vomiting into the trash can.&nbsp; I called the custodian again and he came and took care of it.&nbsp; Meanwhile,&nbsp; someone brought in 5 frozen turkeys that began to defrost all over the floor before the families could come and get them.&nbsp; So I&nbsp; called the custodian and he came and mopped up the turkey goop!&nbsp;&nbsp;

On the other hand, I got to spend an hour rocking a 3 day old baby boy and that makes everything else bearable!&nbsp; There's nothing more inspirational than new life.&nbsp; My job is really weird.

Well, I only thought I was back last time.&nbsp; The remote internet connection died shortly after I got this laptop up and running.&nbsp; But now I've got all the glitches figured out.&nbsp; I have so much to catch up on.&nbsp; I've missed you all a whole lot.&nbsp;

Work is going well, now.&nbsp; We have over 450 homeless kids since July 1st.&nbsp; It's a bumper crop this year.&nbsp; John is still trying to find more profitable work.&nbsp; He took the train into Chicago to apply for a flash animation job today.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If he gets it it will mean a 2 hour commute each way.&nbsp; But the money's good and most of the commute is by train, so he'll get alot done&nbsp;during that time.&nbsp; He just called to tell me he is on his way home.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Kaitlin is doing well in school.&nbsp; She decided to be a Mummy for Halloween, so we took a green sheet, died it in tea water and tore it into strips.&nbsp; We then proceeded to wrap her up for the party at school.&nbsp; The wraps started to fall off so we glued them to her tights and pinned them to her shirt.&nbsp; It was a riot.&nbsp; She was glued, pinned and duck taped together and still started to shed her "skin"&nbsp; in the middle of the Monster Mash.&nbsp; When we got home we discovered we had glued the tights to her.&nbsp; After cutting the costume off of her and washing off the glue and make up we were all laughing so hard our sides hurt!&nbsp; She decided she wanted to be a ghost for the trick or treating part!&nbsp; Smart kid.

So much more has happened but in the interest of preserving online friendships, I'll feed it out a little at a time.&nbsp; Meanwhile,&nbsp; thanks for hanging in there with me.
